modules.description: Provides functions to parse and generate DOT language graphs, including node and edge creation, attribute handling, and graph serialization. Works with custom data structures representing nodes, edges, and graph metadata. Used to visualize program control flow and data dependencies in static analysis tools.

This module offers parsing, string conversion, and attribute extraction functionalities for graph data, working with structured types like `graph`, `node_id`, `edge_stmt`, and `port` to represent syntax and semantics. It enables handling diverse node ID formats through specialized constructors and supports tasks such as file-based graph analysis or structured data serialization. Specific use cases include processing graph descriptions, generating human-readable representations, and managing attribute-rich node and edge definitions.
